Ossim features the following software components:</p>
<p>

<list>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

 <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../606/1060606.xml">
Arpwatch</link>, used for <symbol wordnetid="106806469" confidence="0.8">
<signal wordnetid="106791372" confidence="0.8">
<identifier wordnetid="107270601" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../668/20668.xml">
MAC address</link></identifier>
</signal>
</symbol>
 anomaly detection.</entry>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

 P0f, used for passive <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../484/22484.xml">
OS</link> detection and OS change analysis.</entry>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

 Pads, used for service anomaly detection.</entry>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

 <software wordnetid="106566077" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../166/733166.xml">
Nessus</link></software>
, used for vulnerability assessment and for cross correlation (<event wordnetid="100029378" confidence="0.8">
<act wordnetid="100030358" confidence="0.8">
<psychological_feature wordnetid="100023100" confidence="0.8">
<procedure wordnetid="101023820" confidence="0.8">
<activity wordnetid="100407535" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../021/113021.xml">
Intrusion detection system</link></activity>
</procedure>
</psychological_feature>
</act>
</event>
 (IDS) vs <link>
Vulnerability Scanner</link>).</entry>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

 <software wordnetid="106566077" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../864/861864.xml">
Snort</link></software>
, used as a <event wordnetid="100029378" confidence="0.8">
<act wordnetid="100030358" confidence="0.8">
<psychological_feature wordnetid="100023100" confidence="0.8">
<procedure wordnetid="101023820" confidence="0.8">
<activity wordnetid="100407535" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../021/113021.xml">
Intrusion detection system</link></activity>
</procedure>
</psychological_feature>
</act>
</event>
 (IDS), and also used for cross correlation with Nessus.</entry>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

 Spade, the <it>statistical packet anomaly detection engine</it>. Used to gain knowledge about attacks without signature.</entry>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

 Tcptrack, used for session data information which can grant useful information for attack correlation.</entry>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

 Ntop, which builds an impressive network information database for aberrant behaviour anomaly detection.</entry>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

 <software wordnetid="106566077" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../571/855571.xml">
Nagios</link></software>
, used to monitor host and service availability information based on a host asset database.</entry>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

 Osiris, a <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../224/1189224.xml">
Host-based intrusion detection system</link> (HIDS). </entry>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

 Snare, a log collector for windows systems.</entry>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

 OSSEC, a host based IDS.</entry>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

 OSSIM also includes self developed tools, the most important being a generic correlation engine with logical directive support and logs integration with plugins.</entry>
</list>
